article.headline: St. Francis, Pa. 76, St. Bonaventure 54
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. (AP) -- Sophomore point guard Cale Nelson scored a career-high 21 points to lead St. Francis, Pa., to a 76-54 win over St. Bonaventure on Monday. Nelson hit two quick 3-pointers to take the Red Flash (2-0) to a 10-2 lead over the Bonnies (2-2). The Red Flash led 39-23 at halftime and stretched the margin to as high as 29 points in the second half. Nelson also had seven rebounds and five assists, both career highs. He started in place of Marquis Ford, who was suspended by the NCAA for five games for participating in an unsanctioned summer league. Devin Sweetney had 15 points and 11 rebounds for St. Francis, while Chris Berry added 13 points and J.R. Enright 11. Paul Williams had 11 points and 12 rebounds for St. Bonaventure, and Tyler Ralph led the Bonnies with 12 points.
